      <body>
         <div>
            <head>Translated parts</head>
            <p xml:id="KR3a0002-start">
               <seg corresp="#KR3a0002_tls_001-5a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="zadrapa" modified="2019-12-02T17:55:11.679+09:00">                                    and when fish is rotten it produces worms.</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3a0002_tls_001-6a.39" xml:lang="en" resp="zadrapa" modified="2019-12-02T21:43:30.771+09:00">                                    while the flying squirrel has five skills eeks out a hard life in extremity.</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3a0002_tls_001-12a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="zadrapa" modified="2020-01-14T18:33:23.116+09:00">                                    then to the end of his generation and to the end of his days / (Note: emend 沒世 to 末世 according to standard editions and reattribute)</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3a0002_tls_027-91a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-01-31T21:13:08.79+09:00">                                    If the people are smugly self- satisfied, then laws and standards will be allowed to go to ruin.</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3a0002_tls_006-1a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="chris" modified="2020-02-01T21:03:28.431+09:00">                                    Such men are personally insidious and ostentatious, conceited and vulgar,</seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR3a0002_tls_017-1a.24" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-03-08T19:39:14.591+09:00">there will be sickness when neither heat nor cold has reached you,</seg>
            <seg corresp="#KR3a0002_tls_029-6a.28" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-21T18:26:26.197+09:00">The wise man understands himself</seg><seg corresp="#KR3a0002_tls_029-6a.29" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-21T18:27:24.191+09:00">and the kind-hearted man cultivates himself with care.</seg><seg corresp="#KR3a0002_tls_002-2a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#zadrapa" modified="2020-05-20T18:27:45.81+09:00">The measures to be good in any respect:</seg><seg corresp="#KR3a0002_tls_002-7a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#zadrapa" modified="2020-05-25T04:12:14.187+09:00">頃: mistake for 項</seg><seg corresp="#KR3a0002_tls_002-7a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#zadrapa" modified="2020-05-25T05:07:38.462+09:00">此俗: mistake for 比俗</seg><seg corresp="#KR3a0002_tls_002-6a.21" xml:lang="en" resp="#zadrapa" modified="2020-05-25T15:23:13.547+09:00"/><seg corresp="#KR3a0002_tls_002-8a.42" xml:lang="en" resp="#zadrapa" modified="2020-05-27T16:25:59.919+09:00"/><seg corresp="#KR3a0002_tls_002-8a.41" xml:lang="en" resp="#zadrapa" modified="2020-05-27T16:26:03.276+09:00">足 is most probably excrescent</seg><seg corresp="#KR3a0002_tls_002-10a.23" xml:lang="en" resp="#zadrapa" modified="2020-05-28T19:32:39.661+09:00">法禮:  standard editions 禮法, but disputed</seg><seg corresp="#KR3a0002_tls_003-2a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#zadrapa" modified="2020-05-29T18:43:31.991+09:00">和: considered by most as mistake for 知</seg><seg corresp="#KR3a0002_tls_003-5a.25" xml:lang="en" resp="#zadrapa" modified="2020-06-01T15:30:07.079+09:00">故 is probably excrescent</seg><seg corresp="#KR3a0002_tls_003-6a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#zadrapa" modified="2020-06-01T16:27:59.026+09:00">理 disputed</seg><seg corresp="#KR3a0002_tls_003-6a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#zadrapa" modified="2020-06-01T16:21:34.989+09:00">敬 disputed</seg><seg corresp="#KR3a0002_tls_003-11a.24" xml:lang="en" resp="#zadrapa" modified="2020-06-09T17:59:07.782+09:00">竭: loan for 揭</seg><seg corresp="#KR3a0002_tls_003-13a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#zadrapa" modified="2020-06-11T15:52:51.384+09:00">大陷: mistake for 失陷</seg><seg corresp="#KR3a0002_tls_004-3a.18" xml:lang="en" resp="#zadrapa" modified="2020-06-17T15:18:33.628+09:00">憂: mistake for 下</seg><seg corresp="#KR3a0002_tls_004-3a.27" xml:lang="en" resp="#zadrapa" modified="2020-06-17T15:19:10.916+09:00">憂: mistake for 下</seg><seg corresp="#KR3a0002_tls_004-3a.40" xml:lang="en" resp="#zadrapa" modified="2020-06-17T15:19:23.217+09:00">憂: mistake for 下</seg><seg corresp="#KR3a0002_tls_004-4a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#zadrapa" modified="2020-06-17T18:10:33.221+09:00">很 is a conjecture: originally and not necessarily a corruption 振</seg><seg corresp="#KR3a0002_tls_004-4a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#zadrapa" modified="2020-06-17T18:11:25.858+09:00">為事利: suspect to be excrescent characters</seg><seg corresp="#KR3a0002_tls_004-10a.21" xml:lang="en" resp="#zadrapa" modified="2020-06-23T16:31:05.815+09:00">在勢: probably to be swapped</seg><seg corresp="#KR3a0002_tls_004-10a.38" xml:lang="en" resp="#zadrapa" modified="2020-06-24T01:34:26.562+09:00">成乎脩脩之為: problematic line, but at least 成乎脩 seems to be rather uncontroversial</seg><seg corresp="#KR3a0002_tls_004-12a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#zadrapa" modified="2020-12-04T05:37:43.894+09:00">使 should be 使有</seg><seg corresp="#KR3a0002_tls_008-13a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#zadrapa" modified="2022-01-12T23:12:05.5+09:00">/有 is probably excrescent, missing in many standard prints/</seg><seg corresp="#KR3a0002_tls_008-13a.37" xml:lang="en" resp="#zadrapa" modified="2022-01-25T19:09:03.865+09:00">/textologically problematic passus; e.g. Zhang Jue emends: </seg><seg corresp="#KR3a0002_tls_008-17a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#zadrapa" modified="2022-02-11T20:33:36.422+09:00">/百姓 probably excrescent/</seg><seg corresp="#KR3a0002_tls_008-19a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#zadrapa" modified="2022-02-18T18:43:30.791+09:00">/道德 dubious, probably mistake for 政治/</seg><seg corresp="#KR3a0002_tls_008-19a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#zadrapa" modified="2022-02-18T18:50:47.315+09:00">/臣 probably a mistake for 巨/</seg><seg corresp="#KR3a0002_tls_008-19a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2022-02-18T20:45:19.82+09:00">In discussing the demands of one's aspirations</seg><seg corresp="#KR3a0002_tls_002-4a.21" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-04T21:41:48.288+09:00">As a general principle, as for the arts of governing the qi and of nourishing the mind</seg><seg corresp="#KR3a0002_tls_002-4a.22" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-04T21:42:11.096+09:00">no way is more direct that to follow ritual propriety</seg><seg corresp="#KR3a0002_tls_002-4a.23" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-04T21:42:29.968+09:00">and nothing is more crucial than to find the right teacher</seg><seg corresp="#KR3a0002_tls_002-4a.24" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-04T21:44:18.319+09:00">and nothing is more spiritually relevant than focussing one's preferences.</seg><seg corresp="#KR3a0002_tls_027-102a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-04T23:14:35.241+09:00">Things base themselves on what they come from</seg><seg corresp="#KR3a0002_tls_027-102a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-04T23:23:07.74+09:00">and this is what in turn returns to the same process/does the same thing again. [i.e. the 乘 itself is conditioned by its own other 乘  so that we have a chain of conditioning by 乘.]</seg></p>
         </div>
